    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-05-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="226"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                <head>226. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName>) to Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>, Secretary of the Treasury
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWM_1">Blumenthal</persName>, Secretary of Commerce
                        <persName corresp="#p_KJM_1">Kreps</persName>, and the Special
                    Representative for Trade Negotiations (<persName corresp="#p_SRS_1"
                        >Strauss</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d226fn1">Source:
                        Carter Library, National Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Brzezinski
                        Office File, Box 38, Brzezinski Office File Country Chron., Panama, 1-7/79.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-05-15">May 15, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_US_2">U.S.</gloss> Investment Team to Panama</item>
                </list>
                <p>In his meeting with Panamanian President <persName corresp="#p_RA_1"
                        >Royo</persName>, on May 10, 1979,<note n="2" xml:id="d226fn2">See <ref
                            target="#d224">Document 224</ref>.</note> President <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> agreed to <persName corresp="#p_RA_1"
                        >Royo</persName>’s suggestion that the <gloss target="#t_US_2">U.S.</gloss>
                    government send a high-level team to Panama to encourage <gloss target="#t_US_2"
                        >U.S.</gloss> investment and trade with that country. Both Presidents
                    referred to the <persName corresp="#p_SRS_1">Strauss</persName> Mission to Egypt
                    and Israel as an example of the kind of mission the <gloss target="#t_US_2"
                        >U.S.</gloss> should <pb facs="0594" n="559" xml:id="pg_559"/> send to
                        Panama.<note n="3" xml:id="d226fn3">See <ref target="#d224fn7">footnote 7,
                            Document 224</ref>.</note> The State Department should coordinate this
                    effort with agencies in the government, interested Members of Congress, the
                        <gloss target="#t_US_2">U.S.</gloss> business community, and the Panamanian
                    government. Please report as appropriate.<note n="4" xml:id="d226fn4">See <ref
                            target="#d248">Document 248</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
